truction of heaven and earth in the work of Pasolini. Particular attention is given to the representation of the body in his last four films: the grotesque and mythical bodies in popular tradition in his Trilogia di vita and the tortured bodies destroyed by the mass media in Salò.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture producers and directorszItalyxHistoryy20th century. 0aMotion pictureszItalyxHistoryy20th century. 4aFilm and Media Studies 2019. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aItaly of Luchino Visconti.  aItaly of Roberto Rossellini.  aNeorealism.  aPaisà.  aaesthetic resonances.  aantiquarian vein.  aarchetypical image cinema.  acommemorative vein.  agenuine scholarship.  aliterature.  amusic.  aobsessions.  apainting.  apoetry.1 aParigi, Stefania, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152614123140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526141231423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526141231/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles